== JRuby on Rails on Google App Engine - Tutorial

This is just a simple tutorial for putting a base JRails installation inside google app engine.

To start it, you have to run, this following commands(After cloning it and moved into the app folder):


	sudo gem install rvm  //a great ruby dataset switcher. i love it.
	rvm install jruby
	rvm use jruby		  //self-explicative
	sudo gem install rails google-appengine rails_dm_datastore activerecord-nulldb-adapter //all necessary gems
	
then, finally you can start the app:
	./script/server.sh 
	
Head your browser to http://localhost:8080 and enjoy :-).


	